The "Miabi" name and the Miabi logos, marks, and icons in this directory
(the "Marks") are trademarks of the Miabi project. Unlike the Miabi source
code, the Marks are NOT covered by the project's open-source software license.
This document grants a limited permission to use the Marks and sets out the
conditions for that use.

1. Permitted use
   You may use the Marks, without prior written permission and free of charge,
   to refer to the Miabi project — for example:
     - to state that your software integrates with, supports, is built on, or
       works with Miabi;
     - in articles, blog posts, presentations, documentation, and educational
       material about Miabi;
     - as a link back to the Miabi project or website.

2. Conditions
   When you use the Marks you must:
     - use the files provided here as-is, without modification;
     - preserve the proportions and colors (you may scale proportionally and
       place a variant with sufficient contrast on your background);
     - keep reasonable clear space around the Marks;
     - not present the Marks in a way that is misleading or disparaging.

3. Restrictions
   You may NOT:
     - alter, recolor, rotate, distort, animate, or redraw the Marks, or
       combine them with other logos to form a new mark;
     - use the Marks as (part of) your own product, application, service,
       company, or organization name, logo, icon, or favicon;
     - use the Marks in a way that implies sponsorship, endorsement,
       affiliation, or partnership with the Miabi project where none exists;
     - register or attempt to register the Marks (or confusingly similar names
       or logos) as a trademark, domain name, or social handle.

4. Reservation of rights
   All rights in the Marks not expressly granted here are reserved by the Miabi
   project. This permission may be revoked or updated at any time. Nothing in
   this license transfers ownership of the Marks or grants any right in the
   Miabi name beyond the limited use described above.

If you are unsure whether your intended use is permitted, or you would like to
request a use beyond this license, please contact the maintainers.

The Marks are provided "as is", without warranty of any kind.
